Reproduction in different conditions and contexts helps to contrast and compare what works most of the time, some of the time, never. When a program such as our gender-sensitive, arts-aware Kool Routes to Schools works in very different schools, in different locations, during normal times, at home during the pandemic, and in public squares and quarantines eased, we could see what elements were important to reinforce. The Arts component became much more central to the program's resilience and to understanding and influencing participants' imaginaries regarding transportation and neighborhood life. In a sense we were "reproducing", with important adaptations, Safe Routes to School programs from the Global North (UK, US, Canada). We found very important modifications were central for them to work in the Global South (Chile).
